http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Competitive-exam-for-selection-of-assistant-professors/article14011840.ece

The Karnataka Examinations Authority (KEA) will hold competitive examinations for recruiting teachers to 2,160 posts of assistant professor in government first grade colleges in the State.The examinations will be held from March 1 to 5, the KEA said in a press release here.Candidates have to compulsorily appear for the competitive examinations to become eligible for further recruitment process. Candidates can download their admission tickets from the KEA website, http://kea.kar.nic.in, by February 20, according to the press release.